\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{M}_{o}^{*}$
\end_inset

.
  If nitrate is still present in the water, the bacterial rate of production
 of reduction equivalents 
\begin_inset Formula $N^{(6)}$
\end_inset

 is converted to nitrate consumption, mimicking the bacteria-mediated denitrific
ation reactions.
 This chemical rate leads to a direct production of gaseous N
\begin_inset Formula $_{2}$
\end_inset

 in the water, which is the only time rate of change for state variable
 
\begin_inset Formula $O^{(4)}$
\end_inset

 in the model.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
