 are also quickly re-oxidized at the following rate:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left.\frac{dN^{(6)}}{dt}\right|_{sink_{r}}^{reox}=\Lambda_{_{N^{(6)}}}^{reox}\,\frac{O^{(2)}}{O^{(2)}+h_{_{o}}}N^{(6)}\label{eq:redequiv_reox}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\Lambda_{_{N^{(6)}}}^{reox}$
\end_inset

 is the (constant) specific daily re-oxidation rate, and 
\begin_inset Formula $h_{_{o}}$
\end_inset

 is the half-saturation oxygen concentration.
  When oxygen and nitrate are completely depleted the last two terms in
 (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
