 Both numbers are currently unknown, and therefore they need to be adjusted
 by trial-and-error for balancing the iron cycle in the ocean.
 The  inclusion of iron as an explicit component of zooplankton and bacteria
 may link this process to the direct excretion of organisms and bacterial
 regeneration activity, once the important pathways and time-scales have
 been properly assessed by laboratory and in situ experiments.
\end_layout

