\begin_layout Standard
The default basic configuration of BFM is the STANDALONE model, which simulates
 the biogeochemistry of a water volume with given depth.
 The typical example is a micro- or mesocosm batch culture.
 Only the pelagic system can be currently simulated with this configuration.
 The model is forced with prescribed or analytical functions of temperature,
 salinity and light and can be integrated for any desired period with three
 different numerical schemes.
 The model output is in NetCDF.
 
\end_layout

