 models.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description

\family typewriter
BFM_STANDALONE
\family default
: This macro controls the main memory structure of the BFM.
 In default configuration the BFM allocates its own memory array.
 When the macro is defined at compilation (
\family typewriter
-DBFM_STANDALONE
\family default
) all the variables belonging to the main memory are defined as pointers
 and are not allocated during the initialization phase.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description

\family typewriter
BFM_NOPOINTERS
\family default
: by default, all the F90 symbols of the BFM state variables are defined
 as pointers to the main memory (cf.
 Sec.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Memory-layout"

\end_inset

).
 By defining this macro, it is possible to substitute all the pointers with
 the actual memory location.
 For instance, all the occurrences of the keyword 
\family typewriter
P1c(:)
\family default
 which are pointers to the memory address of phytoplankton carbon content,
 are substituted with the name 
\family typewriter
D3STATE(ppP1c,:)
\family default
.
 To facilitate this feature, it is requested that all the references to
 the pointers in the code are written with the indication of the number
 of dimensions: 
\family typewriter
P1c
\family default
 should always be indicated as 
\family typewriter
P1c(:)
\family default
, otherwise a pre-compiler error is generated when 
\family typewriter
BFM_NOPOINTERS
\family default
 is defined.
 This macro is strongly recommended when BFM is coupled to hydrodynamical
 models.
\end_layout

