\end_inset

Layout of the main memory array for the pelagic variables (
\family typewriter
D3STATE
\family default
) and schematic of the remapping into a three-dimensional ocean grid for
 transport processes.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The other basic arrays of the memory are the ones containing the time rates
 of change due to each physiological or ecological interaction.
 The rate of mass exchange between two state variables is an element of
 an array 
\family typewriter
D3SOURCE
\family default
, if it is a production term, and 
\family typewriter
D3SINK
\family default
 if it is a loss term, both with dimensions 
\family typewriter
NO_D3_BOX_STATES
\family default
 
\begin_inset Formula $\times$
\end_inset

 
\family typewriter
NO_D3_BOX_STATES
\family default
 
\begin_inset Formula $\times$
\end_inset


\family typewriter
 NO_BOXES
\family default
 (Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Schematic-of-D3SOURCE"

\end_inset

).
 It is clear that the two matrices are symmetrical and a predation (negative)
 rate from variable 
\family typewriter
P1c
\family default
 to 
\family typewriter
Z4c
\family default
 is equivalent to an ingestion rate (positive) of 
\family typewriter
Z4c
\family default
 over 
\family typewriter
P1c
\family default
.
 All the rates are defined positive by convention, so that to obtain the
 net rate of change for variable of row j, it is sufficient to compute
\begin_inset listings
lstparams "basicstyle={\normalsize\ttfamily},language=Fortran"
inline false
status open

\begin_layout LyX-Code

sum(D3SOURCE(j,:,:)-D3SINK(j,:,:))
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Fluxes which involve a variable not defined in the model, such as oxygen
 production from water during photosynthesis can be taken into account by
 using the diagonal of the matrix.
 There is a positive flow from 
\family typewriter
O2o
\family default
 to itself computed stoichiometrically from the gross carbon production
 rate and inserted in (
\family typewriter
D3SOURCE(O2o,O2o,:)
\family default
, cf.
 Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Schematic-of-D3SOURCE"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The same definitions apply for the 2-dimensional system, and the arrays
 are called 
\family typewriter
D2SOURCE
\family default
 and 
\family typewriter
D2SINK
\family default
 with dimensions 
\family typewriter
NO_D2_BOX_STATES
\family default
 
\begin_inset Formula $\times$
\end_inset


\family typewriter
 NO_D2_BOX_STATES
\family default
 
\begin_inset Formula $\times$
\end_inset


\family typewriter
 NO_BOXES_XY
\family default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This separation between positive and negative terms allow to use more sophistica
ted positive-definite integration schemes, but it may result in an excessive
 memory usage.
 Thus, the default setting of BFM make use of a shrank version of 
\family typewriter
D3SOURCE
\family default
 (
\family typewriter
NO_D3_BOX_STATES
\family default
 
\begin_inset Formula $\times$
\end_inset


\family typewriter
 NO_BOXES
\family default
