\begin_layout Section
Restart
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The length of each BFM simulation is controlled by the physical transport
 model except for the STANDALONE model which has its own time marching.
 It is common practice in modeling to split the simulation in several chunks
 and to continue the simulation from the end values of each state variable
 at the end of a previous run.
 The BFM stores this information in a NetCDF file which is always generated
 at the end of each simulation.
 There is no automatic control on the date (neither it is stored as an attribute
 inside the NetCDF file), so it is totally up to the user to check that
 the initial restart file is the proper one.
 The input/output restart file names and the restart switch (
\family typewriter
bfm_init
\family default
) are set in the 
\family typewriter
BFM_General.nml
\family default
 file within the namelist 
\family typewriter
bfm_init_nml
\family default
.
\end_layout

